                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12916949" author="erans" created="Fri, 1 Oct 2010 16:57:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I knew about this one. I didn&apos;t &quot;clone&quot; because I figured out that one should be pretty pervert to fiddle with data coming from an exception. At that point, the only sane thing would be to examine/print the content...&lt;br/&gt;
So this is an optimization to avoid copying the data several times (see the accessor methods in the subclass &lt;tt&gt;MatrixDimensionMismatchException&lt;/tt&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12916967" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Fri, 1 Oct 2010 17:41:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another way to avoid copying yet still provide read-only access to the array would be to use an indexed getter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That would be safe even for &quot;insane&quot; code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12916985" author="erans" created="Fri, 1 Oct 2010 18:11:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolved as suggested (revision 1003606).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13010383" author="luc" created="Wed, 23 Mar 2011 20:24:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing issue as it was included in version 2.2, which has been released&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
